******
[1] Ethiopia NOT
Date: Wed 15 Oct 2014
From: Akeza Teame <ateame@yahoo.com> [edited]


[Re: ProMED-mail Ebola virus disease - ex Africa (14): Ethiopia susp., USA 2nd case, prevention 20141013.2859164, item [1] Ethiopia: suspected case]
----------------------------------------------------------------------
There has been a fabricated news report that a diplomat with Ebola [virus disease] has been admitted to Saint Yared General Hospital in Addis Ababa, Ethiopia. I am the medical director of this hospital and I can assure you that the information is false and we have never had any patient with Ebola. I am actually disgusted by the people who fabricated this false information.

Please note that up-to-date information can also be found at http://www.ephi.gov.et. The Federal Ministry of Health has also created an 8335 hotline number, which can be used when needed.

--
Akeza Teame, MD
Medical Director of Saint Yared General Hospital
Addis Ababa
Ethiopia
<ateame@yahoo.com>

[We thank Dr Teame and regret posting this uncorroborated report. ProMED always prefers to receive reports directly from the people concerned rather than have to depend on unreliable news media stories. This page on the MoH website gives full details of Ethiopia's preparedness activities (http://www.ephi.gov.et/index.php/public-health-emergency/ebola-updates-and-information). - Mod.JW]

