[2] USA: 1st Dallas nurse will be transferred to NIH facility
Date: Thu 16 Oct 2014
Source: Washington Post [edited]
http://www.washingtonpost.com/news/to-your-health/wp/2014/10/16/dallas-nurse-nina-pham-will-be-transferred-to-nih-facility-in-bethesda-maryland


1st Dallas nurse will be transferred to NIH facility in Bethesda, Maryland
----------------------------------------------------------------------
The 1st Dallas [Texas] nurse who contracted Ebola while taking care of the 1st patient to die from the deadly virus in the U.S., released a statement Tuesday [14 Oct 2014] saying that she's doing well. She will be transferred to a National Institutes of Health clinical center in Bethesda [Maryland], officials and the NIH said Thursday [16 Oct 2014]. The nurse's transfer to the facility, one of 4 in the United States with a special biocontainment unit, will occur Thursday evening [16 Oct 2014], according to Anthony Fauci, director of NIH's National Institute of Allergy and Infectious Diseases, who was testifying at a Capitol Hill hearing Thursday afternoon. He said she would receive "state of the art care" there. Fauci said that he has been told that she is "stable" and "doing reasonably well," but added that he hasn't seen her himself yet. The facility has only 2 beds, he said.... -- more

[Byline: Lenny Bernstein]

